sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/openstack/co.message:
Tuple in tuple can't be used.

class B(Exception):
    pass
class C(B):
    pass
class D(C):
    pass
connection_errors = [B, C, D]

try:
    try:
        raise Exception("YES")
    except (Exception, tuple(connection_errors)) as e:
        print("{}".format(e))
    except Exception:
        print("NO")
except Exception:
    print("FAILURE")

Didn't check the used version vs doc version, but according to kombu https://docs.celeryproject.org/projects/kombu/en/1.0/reference/kombu.connection.html
this is a list, which isn't supported. If so, then it needs to be cast to a tuple.


class B(Exception):
    pass
class C(B):
    pass
class D(C):
    pass
connection_errors = [B, C, D]

try:
    try:
        raise B("YES")
    except connection_errors as e:
        print("{}".format(e))
    except Exception:
        print("NO")
except Exception:
    print("FAILURE")


Anyway tuple(tuple(some_list)) can be safely used.

try:
    raise B("YES")
except tuple(tuple(connection_errors)) as e:
    print("{}".format(e))
except Exception:
    print("NO")

